		 For What It’s Worth: A Review of the Wu-Tang Clan’s “Once Upon a Time in Shaolin” 		 
			 
				 Dan Cohen 			 
							 
					 Art ,  Music 				 
			
			
			 
				 January 4, 2016 March 8, 2018 

					 
	
	 
		 This is what we know: On November 24, 2015, the Wu-Tang Clan sold its latest album,  Once Upon a Time in Shaolin , through an online auction house. As one of the most innovative rap groups, the Wu-Tang Clan had used concepts for their recordings before, but the latest album would be their highest concept: it would exist as only one copy—as an LP, that physical,  authentic  format for music—encased in an artisa